name: Somber Night
description: I took this picture on the beach one night in Port Aransas, Texas. It occurred in a moment of solitude at the beginnings and ends of pivotal changes in my life. I have kept this picture for years as a reminder of how life can change and grow, though the process itself is not always pleasant. Few things worthwhile in life are painless though. I offer this series as a 1-100 mint for my inaugural debut for my works on Hic and appreciate your patronage. I will reveal my identity in due time.
